SIMPLE: full-blown
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Full-blown
<hw>Full"-blown`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fully
expanded, as a blossom; completely developed; <as>as, a
<ex>full-blown</ex> rose</as>.</def> <rj><au>Denham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fully distended with wind, as a sail.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Of full intensity; <as>as,
the recession developed into <ex>full-blown</ex> depression; a
<ex>full-blown</ex> international crisis</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>full-bosomed</ent>⟦br⟧
